text: Sia Kangri is a mountain in the Karakoram range, in China and Pakistan. Sia Kangri is part of the Baltoro Muztagh subrange. It is the 61st highest mountain in the world. The first people to reach the top were Gunther Dyhrenfurth and his expedition, in 1934. == References == Category:Mountains of Gilgit-Baltistan Category:Mountains of Tibet Category:Karakoram
